\p  
\v 21 Forsooth we shall fight for our lives, and our laws; 
\p  
\v 22 and the Lord himself shall all-break them before our face; forsooth dread ye not them. 
\p  
\v 23 Soothly as he ceased for to speak, he hurled into them suddenly; and Seron was all-broken, and his host, in the sight of him. 
\p  
\v 24 And he pursued him in the going down of Bethhoron, till into the field; and eight hundred men of them fell down, the others forsooth fled into the land of \sls (the)\sls* Philistines. 
